President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his Administration. William Bryan, who currently serves as Senior Official Performing the Duties of the Under Secretary for Science and Technology at the Department of Homeland Security, is nominated to be the Under Secretary for Science and Technology. Martin Oberman, a lawyer from Illinois, is nominated to be a Member of the Surface Transportation Board. Philip Kosnett, currently the Chargé d’Affaires ad interim at the United States Embassy in Ankara, Turkey, is nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Kosovo.